Welcome to Fuckitville™ friends, population me. 🙋🏻‍♀️

This is what happens to moms who stupidly buy skateboards from Target and choose pick-up instead of shipping. WITH SHIPPING, THIS BITCH WOULDA HAD A BOX! BUT NOOOOOO, I HAD TO CHOOSE FRIGGIN PICK-UP! 🤦🏻‍♀️🙋🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️

So here's MY DUMBASS in the 7-degree garage just now during this arctic hellish freeze 🥶trying to hunt down the "I'm gonna save this box because it's a good box" collection to see if I've got anything to work with.. 

.. and I didn't. Which you already knew because THAT'S THE REASON FOR THIS POST! 

So that's when I see it. The leftover Army moving paper that the movers wrap all your breakables in when they move you. I've stumbled upon a whole stack of it, and I've seen what magic the movers have done with this shit before! I'm sold right there, y'all! THIS IS THE ANSWER! 🏆🙏🏼🙌🏼

Only, OH NO IT SO WASN'T! 😨

WILL YOU JUST LOOK AT THIS SHIT? 😅

By the time I'm done crinkling all the moving paper, I've gotta go back to the start and recrinkle again. WHYYY DID I THINK THIS WAS A GOOD IDEA? 🧠

Not to mention even trying to WRAP and TAPE the freaking thing! Paper's flying, I'm tearing the good shit AND the crumpled shit, I'm cursing impressively, everythiiiiing's (not) going to plan, cool, cool. 👌🏼

Then I stop to admire my bumpy work. Ahhh, that's (crap) craftsmanship right there, friends. 😉 NooOOoo indicator WHATSOEVER of what's underneath the horrible wrap job, amiright? 😅😳😰

And then I flip it over. 🎁

And you can TOTALLY tell. 😵‍💫

Fucking skateboards and enticing Target Drive Up pick-up, man! 🙋🏻‍♀️
Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays from our house to yours! 🎄🎁🎅🏼☃️

Today, my middle son left for college. 🥹
Last night, we had an EPIC family game night to celebrate his last night home with us before college. 
COLLEGE.

Last night, we celebrated. Having a̵l̵l̵ t̵h̵e̵ ̵k̵i̵d̵s̵ (Baby V was sleeping) around the table laughing and joking into the wee hours of the morning felt like an absolute dream, yet it sat on the precipice of change. 
Last night he was with us, today he leaves. Tomorrow, he won’t be here. Because, college.
COLLEGE.

I looked around the table at each of my children’s gorgeous last night faces and realized it simply doesn’t get any easier as they grow, does it? 
Time fades and passes us by and with it their baby-ness segues into young adulthood. Gone are the baby diapers and kissing booboos, now it’s banking and chores and licenses and curfew and relationships and college. 
COLLEGE. 

Last night was most certainly a core memory, as it was today when I kissed my son for the final time before he boarded his flight to be with his besties. He’s embarking on a new journey, away from home (away from me 🥺) to start his young adult life off away at college. 
COLLEGE.

It’s an exhilarating exciting yet nauseating feeling, friends. I’m overwhelmed with ALLLLLLLL the feelings. 😫🥹😭🫣🤩🥰🤢😃

And I miss my dude already.

Whatcha having for Taco Tuesday tonight, friends? 😍Why not these traditional tacos? 🌮You can't EVER go wrong with some classic beef tacos made with @oldelpaso seasoning! 🌮(Even if I did accidentally butcher the canister trying to open it! 😅🤣😅🤣😅🤣)

🍽 Classic Beef Tacos with Rice & Southwest Veggies 🍽️

INGREDIENTS:

For the beef tacos:
• 3 lbs ground beef
• 3/4 cup Old El Paso taco seasoning (or 3 packets)
• 2 cups water
• hard taco shells
• soft taco shells

For the rice:
• 2 cups @mahatmariceusa jasmine rice 
• 3 cups water
• butter
• seasoning (salt, pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika)

For the veggies:
• bag of @birdseyevegetables Southwest Veggies
• small bag of frozen corn
• butter
• seasoning (salt, pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika)

Optional taco & rice toppings:
• Salsa
• Guacamole
• Queso
• Shredded cheese
• Cilantro
• Jalapeños 

DIRECTIONS:

For the beef tacos:
• Spray frying pan and brown the ground beef thoroughly; drain. 
• Add taco seasoning and water.
• Continue to sauté until the liquid has cooked away and the seasoning coats the beef well. 

For the rice:
• Add water, butter, and seasonings to the water and bring to a boil. 
• Add rice and reduce heat; cover.
• Stir occasionally and add seasonings, more water and butter if needed.

For the veggies:
• Spray pot well and add butter, allowing to melt.
• Add both veggies and season generously; cover.
• Check occasionally and stir well, seasoning as needed.

Once all your components are done, serve to order with optional toppings and enjoy! The rice and veg can be sides or you can add them to your tacos, whatever you want to do! 😋🌮😍

Happy Taco Tuesday, everybody! 🌮

Wanna make a little Valentine's Day fun with your kiddos this weekend? Try our Valentine's Day Heart-shaped Oreo Truffles! 

❤️ Valentine’s Day Heart-shaped Oreo Truffles ❤️

❤️INGREDIENTS:

• 36 Oreos (or sandwich cookies)
• 1 block of cream cheese, softened
• chocolate candy melts
• white candy melts
• red candy melts
• heart-shaped sprinkles or other valentine’s sprinkles, jimmies, & non-pareils! 

❤️EQUIPMENT:
• blender or food processor
• baking sheet
• parchment paper
• V-shaped cutter
• 3 cereal bowls
• 3 forks

❤️DIRECTIONS:

• Using a food processor or blender, pulse your cookies until powdered.
• Beat in softened cream cheese and full blend together.
• Roll into equal-shaped balls on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
• Using the v-shaped cutter, cut out the top part of the ball to create a v-shape and add the excess back into the mixing bowl.
• Shape the cookie ball into the shape of a heart manually.
• Freeze heart-shaped cookie balls for a couple hours.
• Melt a half bag of each of the colored candy melts in separate bowls one at a time.
• Roll 1/3 of the cookie balls into each color using a fork to toss around, and place back onto the parchment-lined cookie sheet. (The candy coating will harden almost immediately because of the chilled cookie balls.)
• Once all cookie balls have been thoroughly coated by the candy melts, take remnant melted candy melts and drizzle onto the truffles and add sprinkles immediately before it dries. 
• Once set, place onto a serving platter or plate to serve!
• Can stay covered in the refrigerator for up to 5 days after preparing!  These make AWESOME gifts for your loved ones, teachers, neighbors, work friends, and more! ❤️

Happy Valentine’s Day! ❤️
